{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "I. INTRODUCTIONLarge language models (LLMs) have profoundly transformed the landscape of artificial intelligence, showcasing unprecedented abilities in generating coherent text, solving complex problems, and even emulating human-like conversation [1], [2].",
    "Such LLM models, characterized by their vast number of parameters and sophisticated training mechanisms, have become central to advancing AI research and applications.",
    "However, the evolution of LLMs has reached a juncture where mere scale in terms of parameters and textual capabilities no longer suffices [3]- [6].",
    "The integration of multimodal inputs (text, images, audio, and more) emerges as the next frontier, promising to unlock a more nuanced understanding and generation of content that mirrors human cognitive abilities more closely [7], [8].",
    "Mistral 8x7B, with its architecture of eight experts each comprising seven billion parameters, represents a significant stride in this direction, yet it encapsulates both the potential and the challenges inherent in current multimodal learning approaches.The significance of enhancing multimodal capabilities in models like Mistral 8x7B cannot be overstated."
  ],
